# Background Color ðŸŽ¨

The `background-color` property sets the background color of an element.

```css
body {
  background-color: lightblue;
}
```

The background of an element covers the total size, including padding and border (but not margin).

# Background Images ðŸ–¼ï¸

The `background-image` property specifies an image to use as the background.

By default, the image repeats so it covers the entire element.

```css
body {
  background-image: url("paper.gif");
}
```

> ðŸ’¡ **Tip:** Avoid text over busy images for readability.

# Gradients ðŸŒˆ

Gradients let you display smooth transitions between two or more specified colors.

## Linear Gradient (Down/Up/Left/Right/Diagonal)

```css
#grad {
  background-image: linear-gradient(to right, red, yellow);
}
```

## Radial Gradient (From center)

```css
#grad {
  background-image: radial-gradient(red, yellow, green);
}
```
